    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-10-31T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-10-31T17:00:00-05:00" n="727"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d727">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.9326/9–3050: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in India</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-10-31T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 31, 1950—5 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>645. Pls ascertain and report nature response <gloss target="#t_FonOff1"
                        >FonOff</gloss> has recd from <gloss target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss> tel to
                    Indian Amb Peiping (<gloss target="#t_urtel1">urtel</gloss> 813, Sept 30).
                    Swedish <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> has already indicated
                    willingness appoint Rep act in investigation charges U.S. bombing
                        Manchuria.<note n="1" xml:id="d727fn1">
                        <p>Ambassador Henderson transmitted the following reply in telegram 1130,
                            dated November 7:</p>
                        <p>“Ministry External Affairs after careful search files (Deptel 645,
                            October 31) states last report from Panikkar this subject indicated CPR
                                <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> was studying matter.
                            Panikkar had reported previously his impression that Chou En-lai would
                            not object if SC should indicate desire send investigating committee.
                                <gloss target="#t_MEA1">MEA</gloss> doubts however whether Panikkar
                            report any longer valid.” (611.9326/11–750)</p>
                    </note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
